\]  
(ΔH = −165 kJ/mol). Deactivation rate follows a power-law fouling model  
\[
\frac{da}{dt} = -k_d a^m \cdot C_{\mathrm{coke}}
\]  
where \(a\) is activity, \(k_d\) incorporates perchlorate/dust effects, and \(C_{\mathrm{coke}}\) depends on local hot-spot temperature via Arrhenius kinetics. Membrane-assisted water removal shifts equilibrium but introduces new mass-transfer limitations at 600 Pa background.

